This paper discusses the development of AI decision-support systems and the importance of avoiding bias in these systems. The paper specifically focuses on text translation as an example, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of AI services and the need for ethical behavior, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), making cs.AI and cs.LG likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of data and the need for unbiased data, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (CY) and cryptography (CR), making cs.CY and cs.CR possible sub-categories as well.
